caption:
time is all you can give someone. 
warm welcomed by sweet boju & baajey 🫶🏻
wanted to come here since a long time , I may be late but what a lovely visit it was. Yesterday morning, had a simple breakfast made by boju & baajey & I couldn’t ask for anything. The breakfast was truly the best. Because they shifted the place just near , we couldn’t got to try the other items. Surely visiting again 🥹

@eatgrubfood requests to stop by this place as you pass by. You won’t regret the company they offer. 
location 📍: SUNWELCOME RESTAURANT (opposite to Juicery cafe) 

I was so glad to see their cheerful faces. They kept on smiling made me feel deeply about what would they have been through & how was it like to..
We could talk with them & they would tell their stories. It was a sad story & i appreciate their work so much. Boju showed us the books & i was wondering what it was. The books shown in the video was written by Japanese author where the author introduced their lodge named “SUNWELCOME LODGE” which they used to run many many years ago. Boju told us that they used to charge 100npr per night for a room. 

🎶 by @asthamusic one of my favorite 🦋

ps. thanks to all the influencers who introduced this place, that’s what i like about you guys the moost 🥰

Bandipur lies in Tanahun district. It is famous for its ancient culture. It’s also an ideal place to break up the drive between Pokhara and Kathmandu while getting a relaxing taste of rural Nepal in the process.

ghandruk :a beautiful village 😍

Follow @eatgrubfood for more updates 💗
Ghandruk village (1,940 m), a culturally inhabited region of Nepalese Gurung community. The village is located in Kaski district, in between Lumle and Dangsing village. It’s one of the most recognized overnight halts during the trekking time in Annapurna region🏔️ People who are going for the Annapurna Base Camp trek, Poon Hill trek, Annapurna Circuit trek and lower Mustang trek stay a night at this place.

Ghandruk village is the most visited trekking area in Nepal. Alternatively, slate-roofed houses, courtyards, a museum and Buddhist monasteries are delightful things you can observe there. They are promoting village tourism by providing neat home stays or cottages. But we stayed at a resort where they also organized cultural dance after having dinner to their guests. It was quite a surprisingly new experience to have stayed in a village resort.

Ghorepani is a village in Myagdi District in the Dhaulagiri Zone of northern-central Nepal. The place used to be a rest stop where ancient traders found water (pani in Nepali) for their horses (ghora in Nepali), thus leading to the nomenclature Ghorepani. 

It will take you through villages and ivory colored rhododendron forests. This is a perfect route for the beginners or those who have very limited time in Nepal. The best seasons for trekking to Ghorepani/Poon Hill trek are spring (February – May ) and Autumn (September – November).

caption:
kimchi fried riceyy recipe….swipe swipe 😀🤌🏻
don’t be lazy….make this & try it out :) 

process: heat sesame oil (make sure it’s in low to medium flame throughout the process), fry sausage or any kind of meat you prefer, toss garlic, green onions, onions until it turns light brown, add rice toss toss toss & then kimchi , soy sayce, ketchup & finally add kimchi juice (which is extracted from kimchi itself) little by little. Let the kimchi juice absorbed & again the juice. Add sea weed (which is optional) . Top layer it with egg & season some sesame seeds & green onions aaaand it’s ready to dig in.

exploring Namobuddha at kavre🇳🇵

Namobuddha is a famous Buddhist pilgrimage site situated near Panauti in Kavre district. Buddhist legend has it that one of the earlier Buddhas once came across a tigress who had given birth to cubs, but she was so frail and weak that she could not go out hunting, leaving her cubs to die of starvation. In utmost piety, the kind Buddha offered his own flesh to the tigress to keep her and the cubs alive. There is a small stupa built in reverence to the ultimate sacrifice of the Buddha.

SOME OF 5 PLACES I VISITED IN DECEMBER: 

#eatgrubfood #eatgrubfoodrecommends 
For those people who are looking for places to eat good food with lake view or roof top view in pokhara. And also with families and friends. Here are some: 
1. @thefreedomcafe_official at north lakeside khahare 
- place with a beautiful view of lake & appropriate sitting space (w/ cabins)
- the biryani & jhol momo was so delicious 
- place to chill with friends 

2. @blueshousepkr at khahare 
- another place with preety lake view & preety environment
- live music 🎶 
- place to chill with friends & family 
- foods here was preety impressive but then the drinks was bland at first & I ended up with one & only peach iced teaaa instead. yaha ko pork tawa chei must tryyy ani pizza ni mitthoo! 

3. @hoteltaskintl at amarsingh chowk 
- one of the must visit place in Pokhara which I have already reviewed before 
- very spacious place with roof top panorama view of pokhara at amarsingh area 
- appropriate for lodging & fooding 
- there foods & drinks are one of the best (crispy chicken & peach iced was soooo good among all) 
- very adequate place for family & friends get together 
- parking for both two & four wheelers available 

4. @dungarestropokhara at lakeside, street no.14 
- great service & environment 
- appropriate for grand party & meet ups with family & friends 
- every foods were served well & appetizing 
- calm music & live concert = good vibes 

5. @jetho_budho at lakeside, street no.14 
- if you’re looking for place to eat thakali khana in pokhara, this is one good option too.

exploring the beautiful village “GHACHOK” 🗻: very close to Pokhara. Probably will be visiting again….as it’s the route to khumai dada & macchapuchre camp . 
The enchanted himalayas are just so majestic, which can be seen from every corners of the village. It is said that 90% of the people living in there can see the divine himalayas from their home & very closely. Also the roads are preety decent. 

Gau ko khana is one of my surreal moment when I visit any villages, it’s fresh, organic & the taste of village is somethiiing & with the view+ the smell + fresh atmosphere & natuuure :)

caption:
places I visited in novembeer ✨

#eatgrubfood #eatgrubfoodrecommends 
1. Family Restaurant at Mahendrapool 
- the chicken momo is a must here with Mitho chutney 🤌🏻

2. Brobakery at Newroad 
- cheesecake & mocha madness is so smooth & rich in taste, must must try desserts here..

3. Calm Pokhara at Pame 
- if you’re stressed out, this place is one of them all….musical vibes & calm for sure. Walnut Brownie & hot chocolate was soo soo fulfilling + the spicy pork && the vieww.

4. Purna khaja ghar at Rambazaar 
- one of my go to place for momo because nothing can beat local taste after all. Momo with the beeest soup evuur. 

5. Brew Tantra at Newroad 
- stopped by & had mitthoo chilly momo at this place…the brownie here’s fulfilling too. 

6. Fresh Elements at lakeside 
- Non-veg platter with varieties of chicken…goes very well with a purfect drink. Don’t forget to try there cheesecake & brownie too 🤌🏻

7. Your’s choice at Newroad 
- because I was hungry ,tried the chicken mix as they serves good food with reasonable prices & with enough portion. 

8. Kalsang pokhara at khahare 
- heard a lot about the place, the ambiance was quite good but seems like the foods here are satisfactory & the staffs would watch you like nonstop 😂 The menu was very vaaast as they serve tibetan,korean, thai & chinese cuisines. We tried some of the foods & the experience was not so great. 

9. Puime Restaurant at damside 
- had Jhir & ginger lemon honey teaa in the cold weather. 
10. Home foods 🤌🏻

caption:
🎣 pokhara fishing park & kitchen (highly recommended place) 
found out the hidden treasure of pokhara (perfect example for quality over quantity)🥹
so much about this place. it’s been almost 1 & half years since the place has opened. my first impression while i arrived there was the ambiance, it was very placid as it’s a best spot for fishing, very eco friendly , very chill place & the floating bridge/path which was floated with the help of poly drums which is what made the place more unique. really loved the idea of it as the owner himself was a designer. the place is surrounded by lakes & greenary, probably a place for therapy 😅 

#eatgrubfood #eatgrubfoodrecommends #pokhara #pokharanepal 
📍 location: on the way to pame (beside tilapia restaurant) or please kindly follow google map 
We tried: steam fish: Rs.500/- ,pork sekuwa : Rs.300/- , pork momo: Rs.220/- 
plus plus points for the foods here. the foods are limited yet very worthy , hygienic & very budget friendly with the best service. another special part is the very unique steam fish with very balanced taste & also the soup+seasoning was my best part. According to the price, the portion was enough & with lots of meat in it. Pork lovers would love love the sekuwa at this place. Pork momo was very juicy & very well made with the best chutney ever. Not so oily, not so salty, not so small, not so thick, just perfect. 

as said by the owner,the place was actually only for fishing purpose & the foods were served for those who come there for fishing. The dishes are limited but has very perfect taste. Foods like bbq fish, steam fish, momo, sekuwa & sukuti,etc are available. The place is also open for any kind of bbq with charge. The owner also speaks about giving knowledge about kinds of fishes to people so that when people go to market they won’t be fooled by fish merchants & also to preserve some of the fish which are endangered.

indulging the pure bliss of icecream, the best icecream i’ve tried so far! 
it’s gelato Italian icecream basically & the best part is it’s homemade, silky, has less calories, & soo fulfilling & rich in taste….overall a perfect dessert in this hot weather. i would probably have it even in cold days because it was that good. the available flavors are choco chips, mango, butterscotch,vanilla,blueberry, mint & choco & chocolate. definitely trying the other flavors. it costs 150 npr per scoop. 
location: 7 days cafe (lakeside: street no.13) 

#eatgrubfoodrecommends #eatgrubfood
